io.netty.handler.codec.memcache.binary

Interface BinaryMemcacheMessageHeader

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BinaryMemcacheRequestHeader, BinaryMemcacheResponseHeader
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBinaryMemcacheMessageHeader, DefaultBinaryMemcacheRequestHeader, DefaultBinaryMemcacheResponseHeader

    public interface BinaryMemcacheMessageHeader
    Contains all common header fields in a BinaryMemcacheMessage.

    Since the header is different for a BinaryMemcacheRequest and BinaryMemcacheResponse, see BinaryMemcacheRequestHeader and BinaryMemcacheResponseHeader.

    The BinaryMemcacheMessageHeader is always 24 bytes in length and needs to be filled up if values are not set.

    Fore more information, see the official protocol specification here.
